In this article, President Donald Trump proclaims August 26, 2020, as Women's Equality Day in the United States. He acknowledges the essential role that women play in the political, economic, and social fabric of the nation. The President highlights the contributions of American women in various sectors, including the military and first responders. He emphasizes the importance of supporting women and working families, mentioning initiatives such as paid family leave and increased funding for child care. The Women's Global Development and Prosperity Initiative is also mentioned as a means to enhance economic opportunities for women globally. The proclamation concludes by urging the people of the United States to celebrate and honor the achievements of women on Women's Equality Day.